Russia Stocks Fall, Trimming Week’s Gain, as Novatek, VTB Drop

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-03-04T16:47:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-04/russia-stocks-fall-trimming-week-s-gain-as-novatek-vtb-drop.html
  Russia ’s 30-stock Micex Index fell,
trimming this week’s advance, as OAO Novatek, VTB Group and OAO
Sberbank declined.  Novatek, Russia’s second-biggest natural gas producer,
dropped 3.1 percent. VTB and Sberbank, the country’s biggest
banks, both fell by at least 1 percent. The Micex slipped 0.4
percent to 1,764.96 by the 6:45 p.m. close in Moscow, reversing
an earlier advance of as much as 0.6 percent. The gauge advanced
1 percent this week.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jason Corcoran in Moscow at 
